Class LinkedList

  • java.lang.Object
    • LinkedList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class LinkedList
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class implements a linked list which will store all data related to sold products. Products sold upon checkout() will be sent here and be either added as a new node if no product exists of the same attributes. However, when the product already exists in the list, only the quantity of the product will be changed to add the number of new items sold.

    • Method Detail

      • add_To_List

        public void add_To_List(Product el)
        This method adds an object to the linked list by creating a node with the attributes of the product and a reference to the next node.

        Attributes of the product will be the same as the item in the parameter. It will utilize the getter methods of the item and assigning it to the attributes of the product in the list. If the item already exists in the list, then the quantity of the product in the list will be added by the quantity of item purchased.

        Parameters:
        el - item to be added to the list

      • LinkedList

        public void LinkedList()
        Class constructor. Initializes all attributes to null, zero or empty.

      • print_List

        public void print_List()
        This method prints the contents of the list. It utilizes the getter methods of the product in the node as it traverses the list node by node.

      • total_Sales

        public float total_Sales()
        This method calculate the total sales of the items in the list multiplied by the quantity of items bought. To get the total, it will traverse the whole list and utilize the getter methods getCost() and getAmount().
        Returns:
        float return the total sales or revenue
